      • embed

        @POST(value="/v1/embed")
 @Headers(value={"accept: application/json","content-type: application/json"})
retrofit2.Call<EmbedResponse> embed(@Body
                                                                                                                                            EmbedRequest request)
        This endpoint returns text embeddings. An embedding is a list of floating point numbers that captures semantic information about the text that it represents. Embeddings can be used to create text classifiers as well as empower semantic search. To learn more about embeddings, see the embedding page. If you want to learn more how to use the embedding model, have a look at the Semantic Search Guide
        Parameters:
        request - text embedding request
        Returns:
        embeddings response

      • classify

        @POST(value="/v1/classify")
 @Headers(value={"accept: application/json","content-type: application/json"})
retrofit2.Call<ClassifyResponse> classify(@Body
                                                                                                                                                     ClassifyRequest request)
        This endpoint makes a prediction about which label fits the specified text inputs best. To make a prediction, Classify uses the provided examples of text + label pairs as a reference. Note: Custom Models trained on classification examples don't require the examples parameter to be passed in explicitly.
        Parameters:
        request - text classification request
        Returns:
        classification response
